prompt:
Grade: 8th Grade.
Learning objectives:
(1) Identify major exits on Sagtikos State Parkway and their usefulness for commuters;
(2) Understand traffic patterns on key segments;
(3) Plan efficient routes between Southern State Parkway and Long Island Expressway using exit data.
Materials needed: Map of Sagtikos State Parkway, traffic volume charts, interactive digital map app.
Activities:
1) 10 min – Map exploration with exit markers;
2) 15 min – Group discussion on traffic volume and route choice;
3) 20 min – Scenario simulation: students plan a commuter trip using data;
4) 5 min – Quick quiz summarizing key points.
Assessment criteria: accuracy of exit identification, understanding of traffic patterns, effective route planning.
